## Dependencies

- **`/blueprint`** — required upstream; reads `studies/<slug>/BLUEPRINT.md`.
- **S12 (study artifact format)** — frontmatter `derived_from` chain enables
  `/clone-and-twist` and `/recipe` to walk back to the source study.
- **S13 (mechanism-fidelity contract)** — TRANSPOSITION.md §8 (fidelity targets)
  is the input to S13 entries.
- **`/plan-eng-review`** — interactive review pattern reused here.
- **`/plan-ux-review`** — recommended (not required) when the transposition
  changes user-facing workflow. Surface as a suggestion in Step 11.
- **`lib/study-artifacts.ts`** — shared parser for S12 frontmatter (planned).

---

## Canonical examples

- **fingerspelling.xyz → TSL** (FAITHFUL or ADAPTIVE).
  - Target-domain invariants: tone markers, TSL handshape inventory, Thai script.
  - Proprietary slots: `tsl-phoneme-encoder`, `tsl-pedagogy-ordering`, `tsl-eval-set`.
  - Domain-shift sentence: "ASL fingerspelling → TSL fingerspelling — different
    phoneme inventory plus tone markers ASL doesn't have."

- **supertonic-v3** (paper inference → fine-tuning).
  - Target-domain invariants: gradient accumulation, training-loop telemetry,
    checkpoint cadence, dataset versioning.
  - Proprietary slots: `training-strategy`, `regularization-schedule`, `eval-suite`.
  - Domain-shift sentence: "Inference-only reference → end-to-end fine-tuning
    pipeline — different memory profile, different failure modes, training-time
    metrics the inference paper didn't measure."

These two are the v1 validation targets per the v3 roadmap.
